President Donald Trump has issued a Presidential Memorandum under the Defense Production Act regarding General Motors Company. The memorandum states that in light of the national emergency declared due to the COVID-19 pandemic, it is necessary to ensure that health and medical resources, such as personal protective equipment and ventilators, are properly distributed to the healthcare system. The Secretary of Health and Human Services is directed to use all available authority under the Act to require General Motors Company to accept, perform, and prioritize contracts or orders for the appropriate number of ventilators determined by the Secretary. The memorandum also includes general provisions stating that it does not impair the authority of executive departments or agencies, and that it should be implemented in accordance with applicable law and subject to the availability of appropriations. It further clarifies that the memorandum does not create any enforceable rights or benefits against the United States or any other party.